    {
      "content": "Azure Search Service REST API: Version 2014-10-20-Preview",
      "pos": [
        413,
        470
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This document describes the pre-release <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>2014-10-20-Preview<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> version of the Azure Search Service REST API, released as an update to the first Azure Search Public Preview.",
      "pos": [
        472,
        644
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Because this version will be phased out soon, we strongly recommend that you use the version associated with the generally available release instead.",
      "pos": [
        645,
        794
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For guidance on code migration, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Transition from preview to the generally available API version<ept id=\"p1\">](search-transition-from-preview.md)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        795,
        931
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        933,
        1020
      ],
      "content": "Other API content related to the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>2014-10-20-Preview<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> version includes the following:"
    },
    {
      "content": "Scoring Profiles (Azure Search Service REST API: 2014-10-20-Preview)",
      "pos": [
        1025,
        1093
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Documentation for the current, generally available version of the Azure Search REST API can be found on MSDN.",
      "pos": [
        1147,
        1256
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "See <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Azure Search Service REST API<ept id=\"p1\">](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/dn798935.aspx)</ept> for more information.",
      "pos": [
        1257,
        1369
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "About the Service REST API",
      "pos": [
        1373,
        1399
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure Search is a cloud-based service that you can use to build custom search applications.",
      "pos": [
        1401,
        1492
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure Search has the concepts of <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>search services<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">*</bpt>indexes<ept id=\"p2\">*</ept>, where a search service contains one or more indexes.",
      "pos": [
        1493,
        1611
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Your search service is uniquely identified by a fully-qualified domain name (for example: <ph id=\"ph1\">`mysearchservice.search.windows.net`</ph>).",
      "pos": [
        1612,
        1740
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "An api-key is generated when the service is provisioned, and is used to authenticate requests to your Azure Search service.",
      "pos": [
        1741,
        1864
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "There are two types of actions that can be executed against the Azure Search Service:",
      "pos": [
        1866,
        1951
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        1955,
        2071
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Index Management<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: This includes administrative tasks that are executed against a search service or search index."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        2075,
        2157
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Document Actions<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: These actions query and manage the corpus for a given index."
    },
    {
      "content": "The APIs documented in this section provide access to operations on search data, such as index creation and population, document upload, and queries.",
      "pos": [
        2159,
        2308
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When calling the API, keep the following points in mind:",
      "pos": [
        2309,
        2365
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "All APIs are defined in terms of HTTP requests and responses in OData JSON format.",
      "pos": [
        2369,
        2451
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        2455,
        2571
      ],
      "content": "All APIs must be accompanied with an <ph id=\"ph1\">`api-key`</ph> in the header or in the query string as described in the notes below."
    },
    {
      "content": "All APIs must be issued over HTTPS (on the default port - 443).",
      "pos": [
        2575,
        2638
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "All API requests must include the <ph id=\"ph1\">`api-version`</ph> query string parameter.",
      "pos": [
        2642,
        2713
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Its value must be set to the version of the current service release, which is shown in the following example:",
      "pos": [
        2714,
        2823
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "GET /indexes?api-version=2014-10-20-Preview",
      "pos": [
        2829,
        2872
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "All API requests can optionally set the <ph id=\"ph1\">`Accept`</ph> HTTP header.",
      "pos": [
        2876,
        2937
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If unset, the default is assumed to be <ph id=\"ph1\">`application/json`</ph>.",
      "pos": [
        2938,
        2996
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A separate API is provided for service administration.",
      "pos": [
        2998,
        3052
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Examples of service administration operations include provisioning the service or altering capacity.",
      "pos": [
        3053,
        3153
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more information about this API, see Azure Search Management REST API.",
      "pos": [
        3154,
        3228
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Endpoint",
      "pos": [
        3234,
        3242
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        3248,
        3387
      ],
      "content": "The endpoint for service operations is the URL of the Azure Search service you provisioned: https://<bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>your-service-name<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>.search.windows.net."
    },
    {
      "content": "Versions",
      "pos": [
        3394,
        3402
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "There are multiple API versions for Azure Search.",
      "pos": [
        3408,
        3457
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "See <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Search Service Versioning<ept id=\"p1\">](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/dn864560.aspx)</ept> for a list of available versions.",
      "pos": [
        3458,
        3578
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Authentication and Access Control",
      "pos": [
        3615,
        3648
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Authentication to an Azure Search service requires two pieces of information: a search service URL, and an <ph id=\"ph1\">`api-key`</ph>.",
      "pos": [
        3653,
        3770
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The <ph id=\"ph1\">`api-keys`</ph> are generated when the service is created, and can be regenerated on demand after the service is provisioned.",
      "pos": [
        3771,
        3895
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "An <ph id=\"ph1\">`api-key`</ph> is always one of the following:",
      "pos": [
        3896,
        3940
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "an admin key that grants access to all operations, including write operations like creating and deleting indexes.",
      "pos": [
        3944,
        4057
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "a query key that authenticates read-only requests.",
      "pos": [
        4060,
        4110
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can have 2 admin keys and up to 50 query keys per service.",
      "pos": [
        4112,
        4174
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Having 2 admin keys is helpful when you need to rollover one of the keys.",
      "pos": [
        4175,
        4248
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Access control is limited to service administration via the role-based access controls (RBAC) provided in the Azure Preview Portal.",
      "pos": [
        4250,
        4381
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Roles are used to set levels of access for service administration.",
      "pos": [
        4382,
        4448
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For example, viewing the admin key is restricted to the Owner and Contributor roles, whereas viewing service status is visible to members of any role.",
      "pos": [
        4449,
        4599
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Data operations performed against a Search service endpoint, including index management, index population, and queries, are accessed via <ph id=\"ph1\">`api-keys`</ph> exclusively.",
      "pos": [
        4601,
        4761
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "RBAC does not apply to either index or document-related operations.",
      "pos": [
        4762,
        4829
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To learn more about <ph id=\"ph1\">`api-keys`</ph> or RBAC in Azure Search, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Manage your Search service on Microsoft Azure<ept id=\"p1\">](search-manage.md)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        4830,
        4956
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: In general it is considered poor security practice to pass sensitive data such as <ph id=\"ph1\">`api-key`</ph> in the request URI.",
      "pos": [
        4958,
        5079
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For this reason, Azure Search will only accept a query key as an <ph id=\"ph1\">`api-key`</ph> in the query string, and you should avoid doing so unless the contents of your index should be publicly available.",
      "pos": [
        5080,
        5269
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Instead, we recommend passing your <ph id=\"ph1\">`api-key`</ph> as a request header.",
      "pos": [
        5270,
        5335
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Summary of APIs",
      "pos": [
        5340,
        5355
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The Azure Search Service API supports two syntaxes for entity lookup: <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>simple<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/dn798920.aspx)</ept> and alternate OData syntax (see <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Support for OData (Azure Search API)<ept id=\"p2\">](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/dn798932.aspx)</ept> for details).",
      "pos": [
        5360,
        5628
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The following list shows the simple syntax.",
      "pos": [
        5629,
        5672
      ]
    },
