        27553
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Filters out Latvian stop words",
      "pos": [
        27575,
        27605
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "All analyzers with names annotated with <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;i&gt;</ph>lucene<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/i&gt;</ph> are powered by <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Apache Lucene's language analyzers<ept id=\"p1\">](http://lucene.apache.org/core/4_9_0/analyzers-common/overview-summary.html)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        30299,
        30481
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "More information about the ASCII folding filter can be found <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>here<ept id=\"p1\">](http://lucene.apache.org/core/4_9_0/analyzers-common/org/apache/lucene/analysis/miscellaneous/ASCIIFoldingFilter.html)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        30482,
        30669
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "CORS Options",
      "pos": [
        30673,
        30685
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Client-side Javascript cannot call any APIs by default since the browser will prevent all cross-origin requests.",
      "pos": [
        30689,
        30801
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Enable CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing) by setting the <ph id=\"ph1\">`corsOptions`</ph> attribute to allow cross-origin queries to your index.",
      "pos": [
        30802,
        30929
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Note that only query APIs support CORS for security reasons.",
      "pos": [
        30930,
        30990
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The following options can be set for CORS:",
      "pos": [
        30991,
        31033
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`allowedOrigins`</ph> (required): This is a list of origins that will be granted access to your index.",
      "pos": [
        31037,
        31134
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This means that any Javascript code served from those origins will be allowed to query your index (assuming it provides the correct API key).",
      "pos": [
        31135,
        31276
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Each origin is typically of the form <ph id=\"ph1\">`protocol://fully-qualified-domain-name:port`</ph> although the port is often omitted.",
      "pos": [
        31277,
        31395
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "See <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>this article<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=330822)</ept> for more details.",
      "pos": [
        31396,
        31479
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you want to allow access to all origins, include <ph id=\"ph1\">`*`</ph> as a single item in the <ph id=\"ph2\">`allowedOrigins`</ph> array.",
      "pos": [
        31483,
        31586
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Note that <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>this is not recommended practice for production search services.<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> However, it may be useful for development or debugging purposes.",
      "pos": [
        31587,
        31730
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`maxAgeInSeconds`</ph> (optional): Browsers use this value to determine the duration (in seconds) to cache CORS preflight responses.",
      "pos": [
        31733,
        31860
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This must be a non-negative integer.",
      "pos": [
        31861,
        31897
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The larger this value is, the better performance will be, but the longer it will take for CORS policy changes to take effect.",
      "pos": [
        31898,
        32023
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If it is not set, a default duration of 5 minutes will be used.",
      "pos": [
        32024,
        32087
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Suggesters<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>",
      "pos": [
        32115,
        32129
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A suggester enables auto-complete in searches.",
      "pos": [
        32131,
        32177
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Typically partial search strings are sent to the suggestions API while the user is typing and the API returns a set of suggested phrases.",
      "pos": [
        32178,
        32315
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure Search is transitioning to a new suggesters API.",
      "pos": [
        32317,
        32371
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Version 2014-07-31-Preview had a narrower API for suggestions where a field could be marked with <ph id=\"ph1\">`\"suggestions\": true`</ph> and then prefix suggestions for short strings (3-25 characters) could be performed.",
      "pos": [
        32372,
        32574
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Starting with version 2014-10-20-Preview Azure Search has a more powerful version of suggestions based on \"suggesters\" as described in this section.",
      "pos": [
        32575,
        32723
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This new implementation can do prefix and infix matching and has better tolerance for mistakes in search strings.",
      "pos": [
        32724,
        32837
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Starting with version 2014-10-20-Preview we strongly recommend the use of the new suggesters API.",
      "pos": [
        32838,
        32935
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The current suggester support works best when used to suggest specific documents rather than loose terms/phrases.",
      "pos": [
        32937,
        33050
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Good source fields for this type of suggesters are titles, names and other relatively short phrases that can identify an item.",
      "pos": [
        33051,
        33177
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Examples of kinds of fields that tend to be less effective are very repetitive fields such as categories and tags or very long fields such as descriptions or comments fields.",
      "pos": [
        33178,
        33352
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "As part of the index definition you can add a single suggester to the <ph id=\"ph1\">`suggesters`</ph> collection.",
      "pos": [
        33354,
        33448
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The properties that define a suggester are:",
      "pos": [
        33449,
        33492
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`name`</ph>: The name of the suggester.",
      "pos": [
        33496,
        33530
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You use the name of the suggester when calling the <ph id=\"ph1\">`suggest`</ph> API.",
      "pos": [
        33531,
        33596
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`searchMode`</ph>: The strategy used to search for candidate phrases.",
      "pos": [
        33599,
        33663
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The only mode currently supported is <ph id=\"ph1\">`analyzingInfixMatching`</ph>, which performs flexible matching of phrases at the beginning or in middle of sentences.",
      "pos": [
        33664,
        33814
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`sourceFields`</ph>: A list of one or more fields that are the source of the content for suggestions.",
      "pos": [
        33817,
        33913
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Only fields of type <ph id=\"ph1\">`Edm.String`</ph> and <ph id=\"ph2\">`Collection(Edm.String)`</ph> may be sources for suggestions.",
      "pos": [
        33914,
        34007
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In the current preview version of suggesters only fields that don't have a custom analyzer set can be used.",
      "pos": [
        34008,
        34115
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can currently only have one suggester in the suggesters collections in the current version of the API.",
      "pos": [
        34117,
        34223
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Request Body Example<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>",
      "pos": [
        34265,
        34289
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Response",
      "pos": [
        35379,
        35387
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For a successful request: \"201 Created\".",
      "pos": [
        35391,
        35431
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "By default the response body will contain the JSON for the index definition that was created.",
      "pos": [
        35433,
        35526
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If the <ph id=\"ph1\">`Prefer`</ph> request header is set to <ph id=\"ph2\">`return=minimal`</ph>, the response body will be empty and the success status code will be \"204 No Content\" instead of \"201 Created\".",
      "pos": [
        35527,
        35696
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This is true regardless of whether PUT or POST was used to create the index.",
      "pos": [
        35697,
        35773
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Update Index",
      "pos": [
        35805,
        35817
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can update an existing index within Azure Search using an HTTP PUT request.",
      "pos": [
        35822,
        35901
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In the Public Preview, updates can include adding new fields to the existing schema, modifying CORS options, and modifying scoring profiles (see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Scoring Profiles (Azure Search Service REST API: 2014-10-20-Preview)<ept id=\"p1\">](search-api-scoring-profiles-2014-10-20-preview.md)</ept>).",
      "pos": [
        35902,
        36170
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You specify the name of the index to update on the request URI:",
      "pos": [
        36171,
        36234
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Important:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> Support for index schema updates is limited to operations that don't require rebuilding the search index.",
      "pos": [
        36381,
        36501
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Any schema updates that would require re-indexing such as changing field types are not currently supported.",
      "pos": [
        36502,
        36609
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "New fields can be added at any time, although existing fields cannot be changed or deleted.",
      "pos": [
        36610,
        36701
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The same applies to suggesters; New fields may be added to a suggester at the time the fields are added, but fields cannot be removed from suggesters and existing fields cannot be added to suggesters.",
      "pos": [
        36702,
        36902
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When adding a new field to an index, all existing documents in the index will automatically have a null value for that field.",
      "pos": [
        36904,
        37029
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "No additional storage space will be consumed until new documents are added to the index.",
      "pos": [
        37030,
        37118
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Request",
      "pos": [
        37122,
        37129
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "HTTPS is required for all service requests.",
      "pos": [
        37133,
        37176
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Update Index<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> request is constructed using HTTP PUT.",
      "pos": [
        37177,
        37236
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "With PUT, the index name is part of the URL.",
      "pos": [
        37237,
        37281
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If the index doesn't exist, it is created.",
      "pos": [
        37282,
        37324
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If the index already exists, it is updated to the new definition.",
      "pos": [
        37325,
        37390
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The index name must be lower case, start with a letter or number, have no slashes or dots, and be less than 128 characters.",
      "pos": [
        37392,
        37515
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "After starting the index name with a letter or number, the rest of the name can include any letter, number and dashes, as long as the dashes are not consecutive.",
      "pos": [
        37516,
        37677
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The <ph id=\"ph1\">`api-version`</ph> parameter is required.",
      "pos": [
        37679,
        37719
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Valid values include <ph id=\"ph1\">`2014-07-31-Preview`</ph> or <ph id=\"ph2\">`2014-10-20-Preview`</ph>.",
      "pos": [
        37720,
        37786
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can specify which one to use on each request to get version-specific behaviors, but as a best practice, use the same version throughout your code.",
      "pos": [
        37787,
        37937
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The recommended version is <ph id=\"ph1\">`2014-07-31-Preview`</ph> for general use.",
      "pos": [
        37938,
        38002
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Alternatively, use <ph id=\"ph1\">`2014-10-20-Preview`</ph> to evaluate experimental features.",
      "pos": [
        38003,
        38077
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "See <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Search Service Versioning<ept id=\"p1\">](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/dn864560.aspx)</ept> for details.",
      "pos": [
        38078,
        38177
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Request Headers",
      "pos": [
        38181,
        38196
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The following list describes the required and optional request headers.",
      "pos": [
        38200,
        38271
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`Content-Type`</ph>: Required.",
      "pos": [
        38275,
        38300
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Set this to <ph id=\"ph1\">`application/json`</ph>",
      "pos": [
        38301,
        38331
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`api-key`</ph>: Required.",
      "pos": [
        38334,
        38354
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The <ph id=\"ph1\">`api-key`</ph> is used to authenticate the request to your Search service.",
      "pos": [
        38355,
        38428
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It is a string value, unique to your service.",
      "pos": [
        38429,
        38474
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Update Index<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> request must include an <ph id=\"ph1\">`api-key`</ph> header set to your admin key (as opposed to a query key).",
      "pos": [
        38475,
        38587
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You will also need the service name to construct the request URL.",
      "pos": [
        38589,
        38654
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can get the service name and <ph id=\"ph1\">`api-key`</ph> from your service dashboard in the Azure Preview Portal.",
      "pos": [
        38655,
        38754
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "See <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Get started with Azure Search<ept id=\"p1\">](search-get-started.md)</ept> for page navigation help.",
      "pos": [
        38755,
        38839
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Request Body Syntax",
      "pos": [
        38843,
        38862
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When updating an existing index, the body must include the original schema definition, plus the new fields you are adding, as well as the modified scoring profiles, suggesters and CORS options, if any.",
      "pos": [
        38866,
        39067
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you are not modifying the scoring profiles and CORS options, you must include the originals from when the index was created.",
      "pos": [
        39068,
        39195
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In general the best pattern to use for updates is to retrieve the index definition with a GET, modify it, then update it with PUT.",
      "pos": [
        39196,
        39326
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The schema syntax used to create an index is reproduced here for convenience.",
      "pos": [
        39328,
        39405
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "See <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Create Index<ept id=\"p1\">](#CreateIndex)</ept> for more details.",
      "pos": [
        39406,
        39456
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        42637,
        42723
      ],
      "content": "Note: Data type <ph id=\"ph1\">`Edm.Int64`</ph> is supported starting with API version 2014-10-20-Preview."
    },
    {
